COLLECTION AND USE OF OTHER INFORMATION / NON-PERSONAL/ANONYMOUS INFORMATION COLLECTION
In some instances, the CloudGuide app may collect non-personal (aggregate or demographic) data through web logs, web beacons and the localization services of your phone.
The aggregated anonymous information is also used to better understand and improve the usability, performance, and effectiveness of the website and the apps, and to generate statistics of how the users use the app in order to provide the statistical data and analytics services to our clients. CloudGuide’s statistical data and analytics services and analytics contain no Personal Information.
Some of the uses of the anonymous information we collect are:
To provide you a personalized experience and show the closest institutions to you.
To provide a custom content experience to our end users.
Allow to share content from the app through a third party social network.
Security of our services.
Prevent copyright issues.
Provide location based content to our app end users.
For internal operations.
Your location may also be used as an additional check for fiscal reasons.
We might use third party services such as Facebook Analytics and Google Analytics to help us collect and analyze this aggregated information.
Please see further details on the data treatment in our Data Protection Policy below.
NEWSLETTERS
We regularly send out newsletters to all people registered in our Newsletter Subscribers file. We do this because we think you may be interested in new features and services, since you showed interest before by leaving your data. Every newsletter sent to you will include details on how to unsubscribe and delete yourself from this file, you can also unsubscribe via an email to .
ELECTRONIC PAYMENTS
Although the access to the website and apps is free of charge, certain parts of content might request a fee to be accessed. If the user performs an electronic payment by credit card on the websites or apps, the personal data will be stored to be able to process the payment, provide the service, and comply with fiscal and accounting laws. The company will however never store the user´s credit card details, they will be sent directly to the servers of the company´s payment provider, Stripe Inc., or the purchase will be performed through native in-app purchase mechanism in conformity with the relevant in-app purchase program for iOS and Android.
KEEPING YOUR DATA UP TO DATE
We need your help in keeping the Personal Information you have shared with us accurate and up to date. Please notify us of any changes to your Personal Information. If you are a registered user, you may make these updates yourself online via the CloudGuide profile.
CONSULTING, MODIFYING AND DELETING DATA
If you would like to consult your data, modify it, or remove some data that you cannot change yourself through our website or mobile app, you may do so by sending a registered letter to CloudGuide SL, C/ Valencia 231 2-1, 08007 Barcelona, Spain. Please indicate your full contact details, ID and the name of the file your query refers to.
DELETING YOUR ACCOUNT
If you created a user account, all the personal information submitted will be deleted. Please, note that we maintain the data collected anonymously about your usage of the CloudGuide app.
SHARING YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION
We do not sell or rent your Personal Information to third parties for marketing purposes. We may share your Personal Information within CloudGuide or any of our worldwide related companies for purposes of data processing or storage.
We may also share your Personal Information with business partners or contractors in order to provide a requested service or transaction, including processing orders, processing credit card transactions, hosting websites, hosting event and seminar registration, providing customer support, providing translations for your content and providing recording services. We only provide these third parties with the minimum amount of Personal Information necessary to complete the requested service or transaction, and the third parties are not permitted to use your Personal Information except for limited purpose of completing the requested service or transaction. We may respond to subpoenas, court orders, or legal process by disclosing your Personal Information and other related information, if necessary. We also may choose to establish or exercise our legal rights or defend against legal claims. We may collect and possibly share Personal Information and any other additional information available to us in order to investigate, prevent, or take action regarding illegal activities, suspected fraud, situations involving potential threats to the physical safety of any person, violations of CloudGuide' terms of use, or as otherwise required by law.
While navigating CloudGuide's web site you may be directed to content or functionality that is hosted by a third-party supplier, not on our websites. When information is collected on behalf of CloudGuide exclusively, CloudGuide's privacy policy will be referenced on the site and will govern how your information is used. For other, non-CloudGuide websites, the site owner's privacy policy will be referenced. It is CloudGuide's practice to require such suppliers to handle information in a manner consistent with CloudGuide's privacy and security policies.
We will ask for your consent before we use or share your information for any purpose other than the reason you provided it or as otherwise provided by this policy. In order to let us know your preferences, we will require an action on your part, such as checking the appropriate option, to indicate your consent.
SECURITY OF YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION
CloudGuide is committed to protecting the Personal Information you share with us and we try to implement and maintain appropriate and good security procedures and practices acceptable to the nature of the information we store, in order to protect it from loss or any form of unlawful use. We utilize a combination of industry-standard security technologies, procedures, and organizational measures to help protect your Personal Information from unauthorized access, use or disclosure.
When we transfer sensitive personal data over the Internet, we protect it using Secure Sockets Layer (SSL) encryption technology. While we strive to protect your Personal Information, please be aware no method of sharing or storing data on the internet is 100% safe. Therefore, we cannot guarantee the absolute security of the Personal information you transmit and you should use our Services and give us your information at your own risk.
We recommend you to take every precaution in protecting your Personal Information when you are on the Internet. For example, change your passwords often, use a combination of letters and numbers when creating passwords, and make sure you use a secure browser.
DATA RETENTION
CloudGuide will not retain your Personal Information longer than is necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected or as required by applicable laws or regulations.
LINKED WEBSITES
Our websites may provide links to other third-party websites which are outside our control and not covered by this policy. We encourage you to review the privacy policies posted on these (and all) sites you visit.
NEWSGROUPS/FORUMS/BLOGS
If you participate in a CloudGuide discussion forum, chat room, blog discussion or review or opinion of any kind, you should be aware that the information you provide there will be made broadly available to others, potentially inside or outside CloudGuide, who have access to that discussion forum or chat room. Also, please recognize that individual forums and chat rooms may have additional rules and conditions. Each participant's opinion on a forum or chat room is his or her own and should not be considered as reflecting the opinion of CloudGuide.
POLICY UPDATES
CloudGuide may amend this privacy statement from time to time, and at any time. Your continued use of the CloudGuide website after any change will signify and confirm your assent to those changes.
FINAL REMARKS
For simplicity reasons, the privacy policy provisions talk about “you” and always use the masculine form of words to refer to people. However, it should be understood that both sexes are always inferred unless expressly stated otherwise.
QUESTIONS OR COMMENTS?
Should you have any privacy-related questions or comments related to this privacy policy, please send an email to . Please only use this e-mail address for informal questions.
